## Interview Questions

### Why must an EC2 instance be stopped before changing its instance type?

Most instance type modifications require the instance to be in a stopped state because AWS needs to reallocate the underlying compute resources.

### What does `instance-status-ok` verify?

It verifies that both the EC2 system status check and instance status check have passed successfully.

### What is the purpose of AWS wait commands?

Wait commands block execution until a specific resource state is reached, making automation scripts more reliable.

### How can you verify an EC2 instance type using AWS CLI?

```bash
aws ec2 describe-instances \
--instance-ids <instance-id> \
--query "Reservations[].Instances[].InstanceType"
```
